entries.meaning: A branch of a tree, bush, or shrub that extends outward; offshoot.
A branch of a path, stream, vessel, duct, etc. that carries whatever travels along the patch, etc away from the main path etc.
(data structures) One of several edges in a directed graph that has an endpoint in a specified vertex and for which the direction of the edge goes from the specified vertex to another vertex.
A branch of a business that has been spun off from the parent company.
An offshoot or outgrowth; something that develops from something else.
(law) Something that results from a law, ruling, or record, but which is separate from that law, ruling, etc.

verbs.description: outbranch (third-person singular simple present outbranches, present participle outbranching, simple past and past participle outbranched)

entries.meaning: To form an outbranch; to branch out or spin off.
